<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 9200 9300 9400 MODELS BUILT AFTER JANUARY 1, 1995 - INSTRUMENTS
        (New Data Link Driven Instrument Cluster) - TROUBLESHOOTING (INDICATOR AND WARNING LIGHT DIAGNOSTICS) - PDL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>PDL</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>2000/4000/8000 Series</title>
            <table id="t0815558" frame="all">
                <title>2000/4000/8000 Series</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                    <colspec colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colwidth="0.51in"/>
                    <colspec colwidth="1.63in"/>
                    <colspec colwidth="0.76in"/>
                    <colspec colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col6" colwidth="0.89in"/>
                    <colspec colwidth="1.63in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Step</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Key</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Action</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Test Points</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Spec.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Yes-In Spec.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>No-Out of Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At forward rear axle and power divider, disconnect circuit 43 from PDL switch and
                                    connect it with a jumper wire to ground. Move key switch to ignition position. Does
                                    warning light illuminate?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col6">
                                <para>Go to Step 6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Loosen cluster, remove indicator bulb and test for open condition.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Across bulb.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;100 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace defective bulb and repeat test if problem persists.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Re-install bulb. With jumper still in place, disconnect connector (28) and measure
                                    resistance from pin 9/circuit 43 to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(28), 43 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 43, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With jumper still in place, move key switch to ignition position, and at connector
                                    (28), measure voltage from pin 8/circuit 28C to pin 9/circuit 43.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(28), 28C to 43.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 28 or 28C from fuse F6, then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With jumper still installed, reconnect connector (28). Does warning light
                                    illuminate?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace defective cluster assembly.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Engage power divider lock and measure resistance across PDL switch terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Across switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace defective PDL switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At power divider switch, measure resistance from circuit 43-G to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Near switch, 43-G to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Warning light circuits test good. Reconnect circuit .</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 43-G or 11-GE to cab ground, then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
